In triangle $ABC$, $\angle C=90^\circ$, $AC=6$ and $BC=8$. Points $D$ and $E$ are on $\overline{AB}$ and $\overline{BC}$, respectively, and $\angle BED=90^\circ$. If $DE=4$, then what is the length of $BD$? [asy]
import olympiad; import geometry; size(150); defaultpen(linewidth(0.8));
draw(origin--(6,0)--(6,8)--cycle);
draw((2,8/3)--(6,8/3));
dot("$A$",origin,SW); dot("$B$",(6,8),NE); dot("$C$",(6,0),SE); dot("$D$",(2,8/3),W); dot("$E$",(6,8/3),E);
draw(rightanglemark((6,8),(6,8/3),(2,8/3),12));
draw(rightanglemark((6,8),(6,0),(origin),12));
[/asy]

An 8-foot by 10-foot floor is tiled with square tiles of size 1 foot by 1 foot. Each tile has a pattern consisting of four white quarter circles of radius 1/2 foot centered at each corner of the tile. The remaining portion of the tile is shaded. How many square feet of the floor are shaded?
[asy]
fill((5,5)--(5,-5)--(-5,-5)--(-5,5)--cycle,gray(0.7));
fill(Circle((-5,5),5),white);
fill(Circle((5,5),5),white);
fill(Circle((-5,-5),5),white);
fill(Circle((5,-5),5),white);
draw((-5,5)--(-5,-5)--(5,-5)--(5,5)--cycle);
[/asy]

The figure shows a square in the interior of a regular hexagon.  The square and regular hexagon share a common side. What is the degree measure of $\angle ABC$? [asy]
